If else Statement : "If else is a condition with a block which contain the statements along with a else block which also contain the statement."
                    1) The condition must be a boolean type in a If block.
                    2) If the condition evaluate to true then the if block statement will execute and the else block will skipped.
                    3) If the condition evaluate to flase then the statement in the else block will execute and the if block will be skipped.
                    4) in if-else statement only one block will execute it eigther if block or else block.
    * Syntax : 
              if ( condition )
                {
                    Statement1;
                }
              else
                {
                    Statement2;
                }


"In this directory there are a lot of program based on the if-else statement and in the future there will be more."
